      {
        "id": "https://openalex.org/W7165184765",
        "doi": "10.1016/j.measurement.2026.122306",
        "title": "In-situ measurement method for cross-media based on multi-wavelength collaboration",
        "published": "2026-06-18",
        "url": "https://doi.org/10.1016/j.measurement.2026.122306",
        "authors": [
          "Hao Zhong",
          "Xingqiang Li",
          "Chuanxing Liu",
          "Rigang Cong",
          "Jinsong Du"
        ],
        "institutions": [
          "Shenyang Institute of Automation",
          "Chinese Academy of Sciences",
          "University of Chinese Academy of Sciences",
          "Shenyang University of Chemical Technology"
        ],
        "journal": "Measurement",
        "abstract": "In the seamless integration of machining and measurement processes, the cutting fluid remaining on the workpiece surface will significantly impair the accuracy of optical in-situ measurement systems. Conventional cross-media measurement methodologies typically necessitate prior knowledge of the medium and struggle to accommodate the complex real-world measurement environments, thus hindering the attainment of precise displacement measurements. To address the aforementioned challenge, this paper proposes an innovative methodology for achieving micron-level displacement measurement on surfaces with residual cutting fluid through multi-wavelength collaboration. This innovative approach leverages the variations in optical path length induced by differences in refractive indices across multiple wavelengths to determine the measured displacement values. Based on this methodology, a measurement system is designed and constructed, and comprehensive experimental validations are conducted to verify the efficacy of the proposed method. Experimental results indicate that under diverse cross-media working conditions, the multi-wavelength collaborative measurement method proposed in this study reduces measurement errors by more than 91% compared with the traditional laser triangulation method.",
        "citation_count": 0,
        "method": "Experimental"
      },
